Certainly! Here is a simple code snippet in various programming languages to create an array of numbers from 1 to 100:

### Python
```python
numbers = list(range(1, 101))
print(numbers)
```

### JavaScript
```javascript
let numbers = Array.from({length: 100}, (_, i) => i + 1);
console.log(numbers);
```

### Java
```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] numbers = new int[100];
        for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
            numbers[i] = i + 1;
        }
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(numbers));
    }
}
```

### C++
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>

int main() {
    std::vector<int> numbers;
    for (int i = 1; i <= 100; ++i) {
        numbers.push_back(i);
    }

    for (int num : numbers) {
        std::cout << num << " ";
    }

    return 0;
}
```

### C#
```csharp
using System;
using System.Linq;

class Program {
    static void Main() {
        int[] numbers = Enumerable.Range(1, 100).ToArray();
        Console.WriteLine(string.Join(", ", numbers));
    }
}
```

### PHP
```php
<?php
$numbers = range(1, 100);
print_r($numbers);
?>
```

### Ruby
```ruby
numbers = (1..100).to_a
puts numbers
```

You can use any of the above code snippets in your preferred programming language to create an array of numbers from 1 to 100.
